mutilated. 
<b>87
</b></p>
<p>  GC Additional Protocol I, article 52(2).  It would be very difficult, for example, for the IDF to 
claim that the whole town was a military objective and that every house was &#8220;by its nature, 
location, purpose or use making an effective contribution to military action&#8221;.  Nor could the IDF 
reasonably claim that the total or partial destruction of such buildings, in the circumstances 
ruling at the time, offered a definite military objective. 
