<b>101
</b></p>
<p>  The two APCS left the convoy at Hasbaye.  There was no truck other than those of the 
Lebanese Army, which were all in the front of the convoy.  Next to the bridge of Kefraya 
(about two hours after the UNIFIL APCs left the convoy). 
<b>102
</b></p>
<p>  Next to the bridge of Kefraya, just before the current checkpoint of the Lebanese Army, the 
convoy was hit by nine missiles.  The first strike hit the first vehicle, the second hit the last 
vehicle, and other missiles hit vehicles in the middle of the convoy.  The Commission was told 
that the cars had white flags on their roofs and their lights were on.  The Israeli authorities knew 
that it was a convoy as it set out on its way in front of elements of the IDF.  The 9 munitions 
were launched in a short period of time.  The 8 people who died were directly hit by the strikes.  
Once the convoy was attacked, the Lebanese Red Cross was called.  However, one of their 
ambulances was hit while the rescue workers were assisting injured persons, killing one of the 
LRC volunteers.  This happened about 20 minutes after the initial attack. 
